hh3cLogicVolume.name: hh3cLogicVolume
hh3cLogicVolume.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cLogicVolume.description: This MIB describes the general information of disk device.

hh3cLvCount.name: hh3cLvCount
hh3cLvCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of logic volumes supported.

hh3cLvMaxSize.name: hh3cLvMaxSize
hh3cLvMaxSize.description: This object identifies the maximal size of logic volumes supported.

hh3cTargetCount.name: hh3cTargetCount
hh3cTargetCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of targets supported.

hh3cInitiatorCount.name: hh3cInitiatorCount
hh3cInitiatorCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of initiators supported.

hh3cSanClientCount.name: hh3cSanClientCount
hh3cSanClientCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of SAN client supported.

hh3cLvCreateIndex.name: hh3cLvCreateIndex
hh3cLvCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the hh3cLvTable object. Reference to hh3cLvRowStatus object for more information. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

hh3cLvTable.name: hh3cLvTable
hh3cLvTable.description: This table describes the logic resource information of a logic volume.

hh3cLvEntry.name: hh3cLvEntry
hh3cLvEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular logic resource.

hh3cLvIndex.name: hh3cLvIndex
hh3cLvIndex.description: This object describes the symbol of a logic volume.

hh3cLvName.name: hh3cLvName
hh3cLvName.description: This object identifies the name of a logic volume.

hh3cLvTotalSize.name: hh3cLvTotalSize
hh3cLvTotalSize.description: This object describes the total size of a logic volume. The units is million bytes.

hh3cLvCreateRaidUuid.name: hh3cLvCreateRaidUuid
hh3cLvCreateRaidUuid.description: This object describes the ID of array where a logic volume build on.

hh3cLvCreateRaidSize.name: hh3cLvCreateRaidSize
hh3cLvCreateRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of a logic volume when create it. The units is million bytes.

hh3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep.name: hh3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep
hh3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep.description: This object identifies if the inquiry string of the logic volume should be reserved. This value of this object is valid only when the associated hh3cLvType is equal to 'serviceEnabled'.

hh3cLvSedRaidUuid.name: hh3cLvSedRaidUuid
hh3cLvSedRaidUuid.description: This object describes the location where the SED infomation is build on.

hh3cLvState.name: hh3cLvState
hh3cLvState.description: This object identifies the state of a logic volume. The value 'conflict' means the names of two or more logic volume are reduplicate.

hh3cLvAssigned.name: hh3cLvAssigned
hh3cLvAssigned.description: This object identifies if the logic volume has be designated for target or SAN client.

hh3cLvType.name: hh3cLvType
hh3cLvType.description: This object describes the type of a logic volume. The value 'virtual' means virtual devices are defined as sets of storage blocks from one or more physical array. This allows the creation of virtual devices that can be a portion of a larger physical array, or an aggregation of multiple physical array. The value 'direct' means direct devices are directly mapped SCSI devices. Because they are not virtualized, direct devices cannot take advantage of advanced storage options, such as mirroring, failover, replication, or snapshot copy. The value 'serviceEnabled' means service enabled devices are all maintained in a one-to-one mapping relationship(one physical array equals one logical device).

hh3cLvExtendTimes.name: hh3cLvExtendTimes
hh3cLvExtendTimes.description: This object describes the times the logic volume has been extended.

hh3cLvRowStatus.name: hh3cLvRowStatus
hh3cLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to create or delete a logic volume.

hh3cLvExtTable.name: hh3cLvExtTable
hh3cLvExtTable.description: This table contains the extend resource information of the logic volume.

hh3cLvExtEntry.name: hh3cLvExtEntry
hh3cLvExtEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to extend resource of logic volume.

hh3cLvRaidUuid.name: hh3cLvRaidUuid
hh3cLvRaidUuid.description: This index is identical to hh3cRaidUuid in HH3C-RAID-MIB.

hh3cLvExtSize.name: hh3cLvExtSize
hh3cLvExtSize.description: This object describes the extend size of the logic volume in a specific raid. The units is million bytes. This object will always return zero when read.

hh3cLvRaidSize.name: hh3cLvRaidSize
hh3cLvRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of logic volume on the specific raid. The units is million bytes.

hh3cLvExtRowStatus.name: hh3cLvExtRowStatus
hh3cLvExtRowStatus.description: This object describes the action to extend the logic volume.

hh3cTargetCreateIndex.name: hh3cTargetCreateIndex
hh3cTargetCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the hh3cTargetTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

hh3cTargetTable.name: hh3cTargetTable
hh3cTargetTable.description: This table describes some information when creating a target.

hh3cTargetEntry.name: hh3cTargetEntry
hh3cTargetEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a target when create it.

hh3cTargetId.name: hh3cTargetId
hh3cTargetId.description: This object identifies the ID of a target.

hh3cTargetName.name: hh3cTargetName
hh3cTargetName.description: This object describes the name of a target.

hh3cTargetMinLun.name: hh3cTargetMinLun
hh3cTargetMinLun.description: This object describes the mini LUN(logical unit number) number of a target.

hh3cTargetRowStatus.name: hh3cTargetRowStatus
hh3cTargetRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the target.

hh3cTargetAddressTable.name: hh3cTargetAddressTable
hh3cTargetAddressTable.description: This table described some address information of a target.

hh3cTargetAddressEntry.name: hh3cTargetAddressEntry
hh3cTargetAddressEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the address of a target.

hh3cTargetIpAddress.name: hh3cTargetIpAddress
hh3cTargetIpAddress.description: This object describes the IP address of a target.

hh3cTargetIpAddrType.name: hh3cTargetIpAddrType
hh3cTargetIpAddrType.description: This object describes the type of IP address.

hh3cTargetIpRowStatus.name: hh3cTargetIpRowStatus
hh3cTargetIpRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete a IP address of a target.

hh3cTargetLvAssignTable.name: hh3cTargetLvAssignTable
hh3cTargetLvAssignTable.description: This table describes logic resource information of a target.

hh3cTargetLvAssignEntry.name: hh3cTargetLvAssignEntry
hh3cTargetLvAssignEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the logic resource of a target.

hh3cTargetLvLun.name: hh3cTargetLvLun
hh3cTargetLvLun.description: This object identifies the init LUN number of a target.

hh3cTargetLvRowStatus.name: hh3cTargetLvRowStatus
hh3cTargetLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the logic resource of a target.

hh3cInitiatorCreateIndex.name: hh3cInitiatorCreateIndex
hh3cInitiatorCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the hh3cInitiatorTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

hh3cInitiatorTable.name: hh3cInitiatorTable
hh3cInitiatorTable.description: This table describes the creation information of initiators.

hh3cInitiatorEntry.name: hh3cInitiatorEntry
hh3cInitiatorEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the creation of initiator.

hh3cInitiatorId.name: hh3cInitiatorId
hh3cInitiatorId.description: This object identifies the ID of the initiator.

hh3cInitiatorName.name: hh3cInitiatorName
hh3cInitiatorName.description: This object describes the name of the initiator.

hh3cInitiatorRowStatus.name: hh3cInitiatorRowStatus
hh3cInitiatorRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete initiators.

hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable.name: hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable
hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable.description: This table describes the associate information between the target and initiator.

hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry.name: hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry
hh3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to association between the target and initiator.

hh3cTIAccessMode.name: hh3cTIAccessMode
hh3cTIAccessMode.description: This object identifies the mode of accessing between the target and initiator. The value 'read' means read available. The value 'write' means read/write available, and write available only for one association. The value 'nonexclusive' means read/write available for multi-association.

hh3cTIChap.name: hh3cTIChap
hh3cTIChap.description: This object identifies the state of the chap attestation.

hh3cTIUserName.name: hh3cTIUserName
hh3cTIUserName.description: This object identifies the user name for the chap attestation.

hh3cTIPassword.name: hh3cTIPassword
hh3cTIPassword.description: This object identifies the password for the chap attestation. It is proclaimed and can be modified.

hh3cTIRowStatus.name: hh3cTIRowStatus
hh3cTIRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the association.

hh3cTISessionTable.name: hh3cTISessionTable
hh3cTISessionTable.description: This table described the information of the sessions.

hh3cTISessionEntry.name: hh3cTISessionEntry
hh3cTISessionEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the sessions.

hh3cTISessionId.name: hh3cTISessionId
hh3cTISessionId.description: This object identifies the ID of a session.

hh3cTISessionConnectionCount.name: hh3cTISessionConnectionCount
hh3cTISessionConnectionCount.description: This object describes the number of connections between the targets and initiators.

hh3cTISessionInitiatorName.name: hh3cTISessionInitiatorName
hh3cTISessionInitiatorName.description: This object identifies the initiator's name of a session.

hh3cSanClientCreateIndex.name: hh3cSanClientCreateIndex
hh3cSanClientCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the hh3cSanClientTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

hh3cSanClientTable.name: hh3cSanClientTable
hh3cSanClientTable.description: This table described the information of SAN(Storage Area Network) clients.

hh3cSanClientEntry.name: hh3cSanClientEntry
hh3cSanClientEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the SAN clients.

hh3cSanClientId.name: hh3cSanClientId
hh3cSanClientId.description: This object identifies the index of a SAN client.

hh3cSanClientName.name: hh3cSanClientName
hh3cSanClientName.description: This object identifies the name of a SAN client.

hh3cSanClientType.name: hh3cSanClientType
hh3cSanClientType.description: This object identifies the type of a SAN client.

hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnList.name: hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnList
hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnList.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Initiator WWPN(World Wide Port Name). The value of this object is invalid and should be ignored when the value of associated hh3cSanClientType object is not equal to 'fc'.

hh3cFcAccessMode.name: hh3cFcAccessMode
hh3cFcAccessMode.description: This object identifies the mode of access. The value of this object is invalid and should be ignored when the value of associated hh3cSanClientType object is not equal to 'fc'. The value 'read' means read available. The value 'write' means read/write available, and write available only for one association. The value 'nonexclusive' means read/write available for multi-association.

hh3cSanClientRowStatus.name: hh3cSanClientRowStatus
hh3cSanClientRowStatus.description: This object describes the action to create or delete a SAN client.

hh3cFcLogicResourceTable.name: hh3cFcLogicResourceTable
hh3cFcLogicResourceTable.description: This table describes logic resource information of a FC.

hh3cFcLogicResourceEntry.name: hh3cFcLogicResourceEntry
hh3cFcLogicResourceEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the logic resource of a FC.

hh3cFcLvLun.name: hh3cFcLvLun
hh3cFcLvLun.description: This object identifies the init LUN number of a FC.

hh3cFcTargetWwpnName.name: hh3cFcTargetWwpnName
hh3cFcTargetWwpnName.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Target WWPN(World Wide Port Name).

hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnName.name: hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnName
hh3cFcInitiatorWwpnName.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Initiator WWPN(World Wide Port Name).

hh3cFcLvRowStatus.name: hh3cFcLvRowStatus
hh3cFcLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the logic resource of a FC.
